main event: On 23 August 1956, there was a sighting of one yellow round object in Farmington, New Hampshire. The object moved south and remained visible for one hour.
interesting points: The object was described as the size of a weather balloon, but its movement and duration of visibility were unusual for a traditional balloon.
The observation lasted for one hour, providing a significant amount of time to study the object.
The report mentions that there were no photographs or images of the object, limiting visual evidence of the sighting.
The conclusion of the report indicates 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation,' leaving the nature of the object unexplained.
The witness, a 38-year-old housewife, reported a clear visual of the object, adding credibility to the sighting.
